So people are being self-reliant, looking for some local/governmental support, or a place in an international project (which is hard). Money is the biggest issue I had to face when I tried to become independent.

On the other hand, government support were difficult too. Kid's fees here haven't been reduced, so I need to pay that first before thinking about anything else meanwhile I haven't gotten my salary yet. How hard is to get a job in France? I've heard about it being more difficult in Europe than elsewhere, so I want to have some plan B.

One thing I did to help myself on this is that on the last few months I've been looking for a lot of job contacts. It was also a way of honing those interviewing skills you've mentioned.

No education related offers so far, but cases of immigration-explicit frauds. So if someone asks me to give them money for a bank account, that's going to be a scam lol.
